&lt;p&gt;FIRE movement
From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
The FIRE (Financial Independence, Retire Early) movement is a lifestyle movement whose goal is financial independence and retiring early. The model became particularly popular among millennials in the 2010s, gaining traction through online communities via information shared in blogs, podcasts, and online discussion forums.&lt;/p&gt;
